<h2>Overview</h2><p>Installing aftermarket accessories can enhance both functionality and aesthetics for your Jeep. One popular upgrade is the Justice Off Road MOLLE Tailgate Panel. This panel offers a robust solution for organizing gear in your Jeep Wrangler JKU's tailgate, promoting efficiency, and maximizing space.</p><h2>What This Covers</h2><p>This article will guide you through the installation process of the MOLLE Tailgate Storage Panel, highlighting key steps and providing useful tips along the way. Whether you're a seasoned mechanic or a novice enthusiast, this tutorial will ensure a successful install.</p><h2>Step-by-Step Breakdown</h2><ol><li><strong>Gather Your Tools:</strong> Before starting, make sure you have all the necessary tools on hand. You'll need a center punch, drill, rivnut tool, socket set, and some duct tape.</li><li><strong>Remove the Tailgate Hinge:</strong> Start by removing the tailgate hinge, which will create space for the panel installation.</li><li><strong>Align the Panel:</strong> Carefully position the panel against the tailgate. Use duct tape to temporarily secure it in place while you make your measurements. Getting the alignment correct is crucial as it will affect how well the panel functions.</li><li><strong>Drill the Holes for Rivnuts:</strong> Using a center punch, gently mark the locations for drilling. When drilling, ensure you use a step drill bit to create the necessary hole size for the rivnuts—typically 13/32 of an inch. Remember to be cautious, as the drill bit should not penetrate too deeply into the tailgate.</li><li><strong>Install Rivnuts:</strong> With your holes drilled, insert the rivnuts and use the provided tool to crimp them into place. This step may seem daunting if you're new to rivnuts, but it's a vital part of ensuring a secure installation.</li><li><strong>Finalizing the Installation:</strong> Once all rivnuts are in place, attach the MOLLE panel using the stainless steel bolts and washers. Ensure the panel is tight and snug against the tailgate to avoid any sagging.</li><li><strong>Reattach the Tailgate Hinge:</strong> After securing the MOLLE panel, reinstall the tailgate hinge, ensuring that it sits correctly without any obstruction.</li></ol><h2>Helpful Tips</h2><ul><li>Use clear nail polish as a touch-up paint for drilled holes to prevent rust.</li><li>Make sure to stretch the MOLLE panel tightly when securing it; this will enhance its stability and lifespan.</li><li>Familiarize yourself with how to use rivnuts before starting. You might consider practicing on a piece of scrap metal first.</li></ul><h2>Key Takeaways</h2><p>The Justice Off Road MOLLE Tailgate Panel is a fantastic addition for Jeep enthusiasts looking to organize their gear effectively. With its robust design and straightforward installation process, it's a DIY project that pays off in functionality. Just remember to take your time with alignment and drilling, and you'll have a solid storage solution that stands up to the demands of off-road adventures. Enjoy the newfound organization and accessibility!</p>

